President Barack Obama has issued a proclamation declaring September 18, 2015, as National POW/MIA Recognition Day. In the proclamation, the President highlights the sacrifice made by the women and men of the Armed Forces in safeguarding the country's freedom. He emphasizes the pain experienced by the loved ones of those who have not returned home and expresses the nation's gratitude to them. The President also mentions the establishment of the Defense POW/MIA Accounting Agency, which aims to recover and account for prisoners of war and those missing in action. He reaffirms the commitment to never leaving any service member behind and increasing efforts to bring them home. The proclamation concludes by urging all Americans to observe this day of honor and remembrance.